00:00:53.655 --> 00:00:58.270
point. So, to find this inverse function we simply switch the x and the y

00:00:58.270 --> 00:01:04.444
values for each coordinate pair. That's how we wind up with this function. Keep

00:01:04.444 --> 00:01:09.994
in mind that inverse functions undo the original function. So, if I put in 5, I

00:01:09.994 --> 00:01:15.369
get an output of negative 1. So, to undo that, when I put in my negative 1 to

00:01:15.369 --> 00:01:20.480
